    <!--Safe Night Tab-->
    <div id="SafeNight">
      <div class="row">
      <!--description of project-->
        <div class="col l12">
          <div class="card blue-grey hoverable" id="safenightcard">
            <div class="col l6">
              <div class="card-content white-text">
                <span class="card-title"><b>Project Description</b></span>
                <p class="flow-text">The Safe Night device is a security system that communicates with a companion Android app using Bluetooth Serial communication. It is equipped with an LCD display, a temperature sensor, and a servo motor. As my first Arduino project, it was designed to secure a box or a small container.</p>  
                <div class="section">
                  <div class="divider"></div>
                </div>
                <p class="flow-text">This project started during the summer of 2015 after I had completed the beginner starter projects for the Arduino Uno. I was inspired to create this when I saw my old grade 6 science project in the closet, a plastic box which triggered an alarm when opened. I sought to build upon that concept using my newfound skills in hardware and programming.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="col l6 container">
              <div class="card-panel hoverable" id="safenightkeylearnings">
                <span class="black-text flow-text"><b>Key Learnings:</b></span>
                <ul class="collection">
                  <li class="collection-item flow-text">Arduino side Bluetooth Serial Communication with HC-05 Bluetooth Module</li>
                  <li class="collection-item flow-text">Working with a Liquid Crystal Display to scroll text and continously display status updates</li>
                  <li class="collection-item flow-text">Implementing a different analog to digital calculation for the temperature reading</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

